Sentencas: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are expected to lower operating temperature and improve reliability.
Titulo: Metal-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells with ceria-based electrolytes

Sentencas: The residual crushing strength and electrical conductivity of porous metallic nickel microtubes were higher than those of nickel-gadolinia-doped ceria (Ni-GDC) cermets.
Titulo: Metal-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells with ceria-based electrolytes

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the metal-supported microtubular SOFC with GDC electrolyte was approximately three times higher than that of a conventional anode-supported microtubular SOFC with yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte at a relatively low temperature of 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Metal-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells with ceria-based electrolytes

Sentencas: The metal-supported microtubular SOFCs have a potential to be applied not only in stationary devices, such as residential combined heat/power systems, but also in portable power sources and vehicles.
Titulo: Metal-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells with ceria-based electrolytes
